    "Body": " Procurement Lead Ripple Foods - Berkeley, CA Apply Now Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $57,000 - $82,000 a year Qualifications Communication Skills Procurement Contracts Analysis Skills Supply Chain Experience Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description Ripple Foods is looking for a Procurement Lead to join our Supply Chain team. This role will be responsible for developing and managing supplier relationships across the supply chain. This position requires negotiation tactics, collaboration, analytical problem-solving skills and a demonstrated ability to implement and execute new supply chain practices. AREAS OF RESPONSIBILITY Negotiate, execute and maintain supply agreements Ensure all suppliers are meeting Ripple\u2019s service, cost, quality and innovation needs Develop sourcing strategies for contract manufacturers and material categories Identify new suppliers and capabilities as needed for product launches or extensions Create KPI\u2019s for all primary suppliers based on input from Finance, Supply Chain and Sales teams Develop and own price lists for each supplier and ensure accuracy for Supply Chain and Finance teams Position will require ~25% future travel Play the role of janitor, receptionist, IT-person, printer-jam-clearer, and general pitcher-inner alongside everyone else at Ripple. QUALIFICATIONS The ideal candidate will have: 4-year college degree in business, operations, supply chain or related field Minimum of 3 years supply chain experience within procurement or planning, strongly preferred with perishable products & co-packing network Experience in negotiations, contracts and agreements Strong Excel knowledge and report building capabilities Excellent verbal, written and interpersonal communication skills Self-starter with the aptitude to learn and develop new skills and competencies in new systems Exceptional problem-solving skills plus the ability to make decisions while effectively implementing and executing solutions Someone that thrives in a quickly growing environment with successful communication across functions Outstanding organizational skills, with the capacity to lead multiple projects while meeting deadlines Ripple still has a start-up feel and our teams are always ready to roll up their sleeves to tackle the different challenges that come our way. The ability to quickly pivot and reprioritize is paramount. ", 
